<div class="navbar">
  <div class="navbar-brand"></div>
  <div class="navbar-content col-lg-3">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="leaderboard-container">
        <h1 class="leaderboard-title text-center mt-5">Leaderboard</h1>
        <table class="table table-striped table-hover mt-4">
          <thead class="table-dark">
            <tr>
              <th>Rank</th>
              <th>Player</th>
              <th>Score</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <% @leaderboard.each.with_index(1) do |leaderboard, index| %>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="badge bg-secondary"><%= index %></span></td>
              <td><%= leaderboard.player %></td>
              <td><%= leaderboard.score %></td>
            </tr>
            <% end %>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="navbar">
  <div class="navbar-brand"></div>
  <div class="navbar-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
          <!-- Main content of your page eg.meme feed -->
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <div class="card mt-4">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title text-center">Le Meme Game Rules</h2>
              <hr>
              <h4 class="text-center">Objective</h4>
              <p>The objective of the game is to create and share the funniest memes within the community.</p>

              <h4 class="text-center">Rules</h4>
              <ol>
                <li>Rule 1: Memes must be original creations. No reposts or stolen content.</li>
                <li>Rule 2: Memes should be relevant and appropriate for the community. Avoid offensive, explicit, or harmful content.</li>
                <li>Rule 3: Memes must follow the guidelines of the platform hosting the game (e.g., social media platform rules).</li>
                <li>Rule 4: Each player can submit a maximum of three memes per day.</li>
                <li>Rule 5: Players must respect and support each other. Avoid negative comments or bullying.</li>
                <li>Rule 6: The game moderators have the authority to remove any inappropriate content or rule violations.</li>
                <li>Rule 7: Have fun and spread the laughter!</li>
              </ol>

              <h4 class="text-center">Gameplay</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Step 1: Join the meme community game by registering on the platform.</li>
                <li>Step 2: Create original memes using your favorite meme generator or editing software.</li>
                <li>Step 3: Share your memes on the community platform using the designated hashtag or submission system.</li>
                <li>Step 4: Engage with other players' memes by liking, commenting, and sharing.</li>
                <li>Step 5: The funniest memes, as determined by community votes or moderators, may be featured or awarded.</li>
              </ul>

              <h4 class="text-center">Scoring</h4>
              <p>Scoring in the game can be based on community voting, where players can upvote or like their favorite memes. Alternatively, moderators can evaluate and score the memes based on humor, creativity, or other criteria.</p>

              <h4 class="text-center">Winning Condition</h4>
              <p>There may not be a single winner in the game since the focus is on community participation and enjoyment. However, players whose memes receive the highest votes or recognition may receive special mentions or rewards.</p>
